<L>Pleas'd with your gen'rous ardour in the chace,</L>
<L>And warm as you. Then tell me, for you know,</L>
<L N="350"><PB N="29" REF="27">
Does beauty ever deign to dwell where health</L>
<L>And active u&s;e are &s;trangers? Is her charm</L>
<L>Confe&s;s'd in aught, who&s;e mo&s;t peculiar ends</L>
<L>Are lame and fruitle&s;s? Or did nature mean</L>
