<L N="355">To hide the &s;hame of di&s;cord and di&s;ea&s;e,</L>
<L>And catch with fair hypocri&s;y the heart</L>
<L>Of idle faith? O no! with better cares,</L>
<L>Th' indulgent mother, con&s;cious how infirm</L>
<L>Her offspring tread the paths of good and ill,</L>
<L N="360">By this illu&s;trious image, in each kind</L>
